Butere women and schoolchildren will be the major beneficiaries of a water project initiated by MP hopeful Tindi Mwale (pictured). On Saturday, Mwale launched water boreholes in 15 sub-locations.Dorice Toboso from Marama South ward said searching for water is tedious work. Women trek for long distances and this conflicts with their house chores, resulting in feuds with their husbands, which can cause separation or divorce, she said.